

small overview how this ontology should work and can be used

should be converted into the docbook description later on.


##################################################################
#
# Conversion nbib <=> BibTeX

The table contains standard BibTeX and several extensions and their Nepomuk counterpart.

  BibTeX	|  Nepomuk ontology	| Type range
--------------------------------------
@Type		|  nbib:bibResourceType | nbib:Book, nbib:Article, nbib:Techreport etc
CITEKEY		|  nbib:citeKey		| xsd:string
abstract	|  nbib:abstract	| xsd:string
address		|  nco:publisher	| nco:Contact -> nco:hasPostalAddress
*annote		|  nbib:annote		| xsd:string
author		|  nco:creator		| nco:Contact -> nco:fullname
booktitle	|  nie:title		| xsd:string
*chapter	|  nbib:chapter		|
contents	|  nbib:contents	| xsd:string
copyright	|  nie:copyright	| xsd:string
crossref	|  nbib:crossref	| nbib:BibReference -> nbib:citeKey
doi		|  nbib:doi		| xsd:string
*edition	|  nbib:edition		| xsd:string
editor		|  nco:editor		| nco:Contact -> nco:fullname
eprint		|  nbib:eprint		| xsd:string
howpublished	|  nbib:howPublished	| xsd:string
*institution	|  nbib:institution	| xsd:string
isbn		|  nbib:isbn		| xsd:string
issn		|  nbib:issn		| xsd:string
*journal	|  nbib:journal		|
key		|  ---
language	|  nie:language		| xsd:string
lccn		|  nbib:lccn		| xsd:string
month		|  nbib:publicationDate	| xsd:date
mrnumber	|  nbib:mrnumber	| xsd:string
note		|  nbib:note		| xsd:string
number		|  nbib:number		|
organization	|  nbib:organization	| xsd:string
pages		|  nbib:pages		|
publisher	|  nco:publisher	| nco:Contact -> nco:fullname
school		|  nco:school           | nco:Contact -> nco:fullname
*series		|  nbib:series		| xsd:string
title		|  nie:title		| xsd:string
type		|  nbib:type		| xsd:string
url		|  
volume		|  nbib:volume		| xsd:string
year		|  nbib:publicationDate	| xsd:date
weblastAccess   |  nuao:lastUsage       | xsd:dateTime

